    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat, then once hot, add your <strong>coriander seeds</strong> and<strong> fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant and toasted, then transfer to a <strong>food processor</strong> and reserve the pan for later</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>chicken thigh</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned</p><p>Once browned, add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Transfer the<strong> browned chicken </strong>to a plate, reserve the pan and <strong>juices</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughy chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to the<strong> food processor</strong> with the <strong>toasted spices</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the reserved pan and <strong>juices</strong> to a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>spice paste</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>browned chicken</strong>, <strong>halved</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until thickened to a curry-like consistency and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once done, stir in your <strong>cultured</strong> <strong>coconut</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Keralan-style chicken curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong></p><p>Cut your<strong> green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop \ufb01nely</p><p>Add the<strong> lime zest</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the cooked rice and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lime & chilli rice</strong></p><p>Squeeze the juice of <strong>half </strong>the <strong>lime[s]</strong> over the <strong>Keralan-style chicken curry</strong>, then cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/keralan-style-chicken-curry-with-lime-and-chilli-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Keralan-style chicken curry</strong> over the <strong>lime & chilli rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
